<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1423,2009]" pageId="10" pageNumber="36">
Description. Thickly encrusting (
<figureCitation box="[590,663,1583,1609]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,255,2011,2035]" captionTargetBox="[226,1360,194,1976]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[226,1360,194,1976]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Phorbas tailliezi sp. nov. in situ view. A. Holotype. B. Paratype" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184055/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[646,663,1583,1609]" pageId="10" pageNumber="36" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
), approximately 
<quantity box="[865,963,1583,1609]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3 mm</quantity>
in thickness, covering areas from 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.25" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="36" unit="cm" value="52.5" valueMax="80.0" valueMin="25.0">25 to 80 cm</quantity>
<number box="[227,237,1623,1649]" pageId="10" pageNumber="36" value="2.0">²</number>
. Surface smooth, bearing numerous, non-adjacent pore-sieves 
<quantity box="[979,1070,1623,1649]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="10" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 mm</quantity>
in diameter. Superficial canals very patent, in the living state, converging into a few oscules 
<quantity box="[874,965,1663,1689]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="10" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
in diameter. Consistency fleshy. Colour of ectosome and choanosome brownish red to dull red in live specimens, cream to clear brown in alcohol.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1423,2009]" pageId="10" pageNumber="36">
Skeleton. Dermal skeleton of tangential subtylotes poorly developed, without palisade around the poresieves. Choanosomal skeleton consisting in loose ascending fascicles of subtylotes and acanthostyles I, 
<number box="[1362,1435,1783,1809]" pageId="10" pageNumber="36" value="35.0" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="30.0">30–40</number>
µm in diameter, echinated by acanthostyles II. No microsclere.
</paragraph>
